<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A four-vehicle collision on Interstate 15 south of Carroll Canyon Road Friday 
night killed a 24-year-old man and injured three others, the California Highway 
Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
Steven Michael Matthews, of Richmond, Ill., died early Saturday at Sharp 
Memorial Hospital after suffering multiple injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Timothy Matthews and John Lentz, passengers in Matthews' car, were taken to 
UCSD Medical Center. Matthews was treated and released Saturday evening. Lentz 
was listed in good condition. 
</P>
<P>
A hospital spokeswoman said Harvey Woodfield, the driver of another car, was 
treated and released at Pomerado Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 10:42 p.m. when Woodfield stopped his vehicle while 
headed north on I-15 after observing an accident ahead of him. His vehicle was 
struck by two others and spun into the center divider, where he was hit by a 
fourth vehicle, CHP said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Officers check the wreckage of a Friday night collision that killed one. 
KEVIN SMITH / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
