<HEADLINE>
<P>
MILITARY PLANE CRASHES IN LESOTHO; 15 ON BOARD DIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MASERU, Lesotho 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A military plane crashed Friday in a mountainous area in southern Lesotho, 
killing all 15 people on board, the government said. 
</P>
<P>
The plane, which crashed shortly after takeoff, was en route to a military base 
in Maseru, the capital, from the town of Qachasnek, military headquarters said. 
</P>
<P>
There were three crewmen and 12 other military personnel on board the 
twin-engine plane, a Spanish-built CASA-212. 
</P>
<P>
An investigation was begun. 
</P>
<P>
Lesotho is a small, mountainous kingdom surrounded by South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
