<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: THOUSAND OAKS HOUSE DAMAGED IN BLAZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire caused $95,000 in damage to a house at 1540 Burning Tree Drive in 
Thousand Oaks Friday night, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
About 30 firefighters from six engine companies battled the blaze for about 40 
minutes before putting it out at 10:08 p.m., said Jackie Noel, a Ventura County 
Fire Department dispatcher. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported in the blaze. The cause of the fire was under 
investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
