<P>
REPORT LINKS HUD PROJECT, D'AMATO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sen. Alfonse M. D'Amato (R-N.Y.) urged former Housing Secretary Samuel R. 
Pierce Jr. to approve a multimillion-dollar grant for a renovation project 
operated in part by two of the senator's supporters, the New York Times 
reported. In a March 15, 1984, letter, D'Amato asked Pierce to use "deliberate 
speed" in approving the 65-unit Buffalo project, which was approved within two 
months, the newspaper said. The letter appears to contradict the senator's 
repeated assertions that he never asked HUD officials to approve specific 
moderate-rehabilitation projects, the Times said. 
</P>
