<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FLORIDA; 
</P>
<P>
DEMONSTRATORS SEEK RELEASE OF MILITANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chanting "liberty for Dr. Bosch" and waving Cuban flags, about 1,000 Cuban 
exiles marched through Miami's Little Havana section to call on the U.S. 
government to release jailed anti-Castro militant Orlando Bosch and end its 
efforts to deport him. Bosch has been branded a terrorist by the Justice 
Department but is hailed as an anti-communist hero by many Cuban exiles. Since 
his deportation from Venezuela in 1988 he has been in jail in Miami on a parole 
violation on a conviction for firing a bazooka at a Polish freighter in the 
Port of Miami. 
</P>
