<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LAGUNA CANYON; 
</P>
<P>
BUILDING PLAN DRAWS 2,000 PROTESTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 2,000 people marched through Laguna Canyon to protest a proposed project 
that would bring 3,000 new homes and a golf course to the rustic area. The 
Irvine Co.'s Laguna Laurel project -- a proposed 3,000-home residential 
community and golf course surrounding three lakes -- "would forever change this 
pristine site," endangering unique plant and animal habitats, said Henry 
Huggins, a march coordinator. The project has been approved by county 
supervisors but construction has not begun. 
</P>
