<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAKERS TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opponent -- Dallas Mavericks. 
</P>
<P>
Site -- at Forum. 
</P>
<P>
Time -- 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
TV -- Prime Ticket. 
</P>
<P>
Radio -- KLAC (570). 
</P>
<P>
Records -- Lakers 4-1; Mavericks 1-3. 
</P>
<P>
Record vs. Mavericks -- 1-0. 
</P>
<P>
Laker update -- James Worthy played 44 of the 48 minutes with a sprained right 
ankle in Friday night's six-point victory over the Charlotte Hornets, so it is 
understandable that the Laker forward was held out of practice Saturday. Coach 
Pat Riley, however, said Worthy is expected to play tonight. Better medical 
news is that Byron Scott was able to play 38 and 36 minutes in back-to-back 
games and not report any discomfort in his left hamstring. The Lakers are 
shooting 44.1% and averaging 104.6 points per game, 10.1 fewer than last 
season. However, the Lakers hold a 249-223 rebounding advantage through five 
games. 
</P>
<P>
Maverick update -- Dallas figures to give the Lakers problems because of the 
disparity in height. The Mavericks start 7-foot-1 James Donaldson at center, 
7-foot Roy Tarpley at power forward and bring 6-9 Sam Perkins and 6-11 Herb 
Williams off the bench. But height did not win out in the season opener, when 
the Lakers defeated (and outrebounded) the Mavericks, 102-94, at Dallas. 
Through four games -- three losses and a victory over the Clippers -- guard 
Rolando Blackman has been the leading scorer with a 19.3 average, followed by 
Adrian Dantley's 18.8 average. Tarpley is averaging 16.8 rebounds and 16.8 
points. 
</P>
