<HEADLINE>
<P>
FALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
WESTLAKE ROLLS TO WIN IN GIRLS' TENNIS PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Westlake High swept host La Canada, 18-0, on Saturday in the second round of 
the Southern Section 3-A Division girls' tennis playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
The Warriors (21-0) were led by No. 1 singles player Jennifer Reese, who posted 
6-0, 6-1 and 6-1 victories. Westlake will play Calabasas in a quarterfinal 
match Tuesday at a site to be determined. 
</P>
<P>
In doubles, Westlake's No. 1 team of Alyse Bartelstone and Alison Levitt 
defeated Krista Stamison and Bridget Sorenson, 6-3; Heather Blanche and Jenny 
Mayer, 6-2; and Shannon Hendler and Alison Horssall, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
La Canada finished 16-5. 
</P>
<P>
In other second-round tennis matches: 
</P>
<P>
Calabasas 12, Alhambra 6 -- The Coyotes (14-0) earned a match against Westlake 
on the strength of perfect performances by their top three singles players. 
</P>
<P>
Natasha Pospich, Stacey Jellen and Alison Paris each recorded 6-0 victories 
over Cynthia Akasa, Wendy Kiso and Anne Leyden. 
</P>
<P>
Calabasas' top doubles team of Samantha Meo and Tracey Paris defaulted to Sandy 
Lau and Uan Huynh but defeated Mai Vuong and Christina Chan and Jackie Uzuhara 
and Ana Chang. 
</P>
<P>
Louisville 10, Upland 8-Louisville, the San Fernando Valley League champion, 
improved its record to 19-2 in a 2-A match as the Royals' top singles player, 
Shelee Gautreau, returned to action after sitting out a first-round win over 
Nogales because of a leg injury. Gautreau, 1-2, dropped her first two sets 
before winning the third, 7-5. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 13, Glendale 5 -- The Chargers (13-5) swept all nine doubles sets at 
Agoura en route to a quarterfinal berth in the 3-A playoffs. Agoura will play 
Dana Hills on Tuesday at a site to be determined by today's coin flip. 
</P>
<P>
Girls' Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
La Reina d. Apple Valley, 5-15, 15-6, 16-14, 15-2 -- Carolyn Russo had 15 kills 
and Sheri Sisko added seven in the 2-A Division second-round playoff match at 
Apple Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Men's Basketball 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 96, Fullerton 74 -- Freshman point guard Sam Crawford scored 14 of his 
game-high 26 points in the second half for the Raiders (2-0) in the 
championship game of the Mt. San Antonio College tournament. Crawford, the 
tournament's MVP, also handed out 12 assists and had six steals. 
</P>
<P>
Roger Thomas scored 21 points and Charlie Cangelosi added 17 for Moorpark, 
which outrebounded Fullerton, 35-29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
