<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
8-MAN LARGE DIVISION PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Flintridge Prep 23, Faith Baptist 14 -- The Rebels had lost to Faith Baptist by 
17 points in the regular season and trailed, 14-0, late in the first half at 
Faith Baptist before rallying. 
</P>
<P>
Running back John Garrett's four-yard run capped an 11-play, 67-yard drive that 
had begun at the outset of the fourth quarter to give Flintridge Prep a 16-14 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
The Rebels regained possession when Faith Baptist failed to convert on fourth 
down from its 29. Six plays later, Paul Park scored on a two-yard run to 
complete the scoring with 2:13 left. 
</P>
<P>
Faith Baptist quarterback Gavin Amos, who completed nine of 19 passes for 117 
yards, threw interceptions on the Contenders' next two possessions. 
</P>
<P>
Third-seeded Faith Baptist (7-2) built a 14-0 lead in the second quarter on a 
12-yard touchdown run by Amos and a 21-yard scoring pass from Amos to Alex 
Estrada. 
</P>
<P>
But Flintridge Prep (7-2) scored on the final play of the first half on J. J. 
Robinson's one-yard run, then limited the Contenders to 72 total yards in the 
second half. DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
