<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Poway defeated Monte Vista, 15-0, 15-4, 15-8, in the San Diego Section Division 
I quarterfinals. No. 1 Poway (29-0) will play San Dieguito (28-6) in the 
semifinals Wednesday. San Dieguito defeated Point Loma, 15-13, 15-4, 9-15, 
15-5. Paige Strayer had 11 kills and Lea Gregor had seven for the Mustangs. 
</P>
<P>
Torrey Pines defeated Mt. Carmel, 15-12, 15-10, 15-10. Amy Peters had 11 kills 
and Christy Peters had 10 for No. 2 Torrey Pines (22-2). 
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals, Torrey Pines will play Helix, which defeated Bonita Vista, 
15-13, 6-15, 9-15, 16-14, 15-3. 
</P>
<P>
Water Polo 
</P>
<P>
Coronado, defending San Diego Section champions the past two years, defeated 
Crawford, 32-1, in the first round of the water polo playoffs. Coronado (23-3) 
was led by Tom Mitchell with seven goals and Chris Cote with six. 
</P>
<P>
Coronado will play Vista (13-11) in the quarterfinals Tuesday. Vista defeated 
Fallbrook, 15-14, in sudden death overtime. 
</P>
<P>
USDHS, led by Brian Clemmons with eight goals, defeated Army-Navy, 20-6. Graham 
Freer added four goals for USDHS (16-2). USDHS will play Monte Vista (15-4), 
which defeated La Jolla, 13-5. Mike Poulson had five goals for Monte Vista. 
</P>
<P>
Chuck Snay and Chad Aronen each had eight goals in Poway's 35-9 victory over 
Mar Vista. Poway (23-2) will play Mira Mesa (17-6-1), which defeated Mt. 
Carmel, 12-11. 
</P>
<P>
Mike McLean scored five goals and Danny Kolker scored three in Valhalla's 24-8 
victory over San Pasqual (16-7). Valhalla (21-3) will play Mt. Miguel (14-6-1), 
which defeated Bonita Vista, 11-9. 
</P>
