<P>
MIRALESTE PLAYOFF HOPES DWINDLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Miraleste High School's football team lost, 41-21, to visiting Whittier 
Christian on Saturday and saw its hope of an at-large berth in the Southern 
Section Division IX playoffs fade. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't think we'll be in the playoffs," Coach Todd DeAngelis said of his 
Marauders, who finished the season 5-4 (3-3 in the Olympic League). 
</P>
<P>
Injured Miraleste tailback Dan Sarner rushed for 130 yards in 11 carries, 
including an 80-yard TD run, and caught two passes for 78 more yards. 
</P>
<P>
The Marauders held Whittier Christian fullback Ron Papazian to 77 yards, but 
tailback Scott Jordan had 200 yards in 31 carries and two touchdowns. 
Quarterback Nick Sanchez hit flanker Alex Davila for 109 yards and three 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
The Olympic League is guaranteed only two playoff berths in Division IX, and 
those are going to Whittier Christian (10-0, 6-0) and Valley Christian (9-1, 
5-1). For Miraleste to get in, Southern Section officials would have to tag 
both the league's third-place team, Santa Margarita (7-3, 6-2), and Miraleste 
as at-large selections. STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
