<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIRALESTE WATER POLO TEAM ADVANCES IN CIF 2-A PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG GONZALEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Miraleste High advanced to the quarterfinals of the CIF Southern Section 2-A 
water polo playoffs Saturday by beating an aggressive Alhambra team, 16-14, at 
Alhambra Park. 
</P>
<P>
Miraleste, 21-5, will face the winner of the Cabrillo-San Marino match Tuesday 
at a site to be determined. Alhambra, the Foothill League champions, ended the 
year 11-2. 
</P>
<P>
Alhambra's Rolando Rojas scored to give the Moors a 1-0 lead, but then 
Miraleste scored six unanswered goals, including two by Brian Johnston, to take 
control. 
</P>
<P>
Miraleste led 7-4 after two quarters, but goals by Alhambra's Victor Arrelano 
and Sandor Poka narrowed the lead to 7-6 with 3:35 to go in the third period. 
</P>
<P>
Miraleste led by two goals six times after that, but Alhambra kept coming back. 
"We need to improve on defense," Miraleste Coach Chick McIlroy said. 
</P>
<P>
Miraleste finally scored two goals in a row in the fourth quarter, when Zoltan 
Gyurko and Andy Foster scored with 3:20 and 3:02 left, making the score 14-11. 
</P>
<P>
Alhambra trimmed the lead to two, but late goals by Gyurko and Brad Youngren 
secured the win. 
</P>
<P>
McIlroy said Alhambra's tenacity forced his players to work harder. "Our guys 
realized they were in the playoffs," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Miraleste's Kyle Hildebrand led all scorers with six goals. GREG GONZALEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
