<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Big West water polo: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 12, Fresno State 6 -- Second-ranked UC Irvine (22-6, 6-2) scored six 
goals in the second quarter to roll to victory at Heritage Park. 
</P>
<P>
Seniors Tom Warde and Julian Harvey led second-ranked Irvine with four goals 
each. Irvine improved to 22-6 overall and 6-2 in the Big West. Fresno State 
dropped to 9-20 and 0-9. 
</P>
<P>
In Big West women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach State 3, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Cal State Long Beach 
(21-4, 12-4) was led by Tara Cross' 22 kills and swept Cal State Fullerton 
(7-19, 1-14), 15-8, 15-4, 15-11. Susan Herman had 14 kills for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State 3, UC Irvine 1 -- Kim Collins had 11 kills and 12 digs for host 
UC Irvine (17-13, 5-11), but San Diego State swept, 12-15, 16-14, 15-5. 
</P>
<P>
In women's cross-country, Buffy Rabbitt won the individual championship, 
running the 5,000-meter course in 16 minutes 53.7 seconds, to help UC Irvine 
women finish second to Washington in the Region 8 championships at Fresno's 
Woodward Park and qualify for the National Collegiate Athletic Assn. team 
championships. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine, No. 7 in the nation, scored 83 points. Washington won with 75 points. 
</P>
<P>
Rabbitt had a time of 16 minutes 53.7 seconds on the 5,000-meter course. 
Teammate Brigid Stirling finished ninth in 17:32.6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
