<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
First at Venice -- Director Dennis Hopper was quoted in a Nov. 5 article as 
saying that his 1971 "The Last Movie" made him the first American to win the 
Venice Film Festival. In fact, John Cassavetes was the first American to win at 
Venice, and he did it twice before Hopper showed up -- for "Shadows" in 1960 
and "Faces" in 1968. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Correction #YES# 
</P>
