<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAR MAY HAVE LED TO BICYCLIST'S CRASH INTO TREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENA PARK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are seeking witnesses to a bicycle accident in Buena Park involving a 
17-year-old boy who hit a tree -- and who may have been forced off the road by 
a car. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Kim of Buena Park was in critical but stable condition, complaining of 
head and neck injuries after the accident at La Palma Avenue and El Monte 
Drive, a police spokeswoman said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman said Kim told police that he was riding his bike to the library 
about 11:30 a.m. Friday when a car came at him and he hit the tree. 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park police said they would like anyone who may have seen the accident to 
call the department. In particular, they are interested in talking with a woman 
who phoned the police 911 emergency hot line to report the accident but was not 
at the scene when officers and paramedics arrived. 
</P>
</TEXT>
