<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVE-BY SHOOTING INJURES WOMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santa Ana woman was being kept alive by life support systems Saturday morning 
after being shot in the head by someone in a passing car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Ygnacia Cisneros, 37, was shot about 11:30 p.m. Friday at 1200 S. Standard Ave. 
while traveling with an unidentified female cousin in a compact pickup driven 
by a 23-year-old male friend, Sgt. Dick Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
An auto pulled up beside them on the driver's side and someone fired at least 
twice into the cab, striking Cisneros, he said. 
</P>
<P>
She was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange, placed on life-support systems 
and listed in critical condition. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting occurred after an argument in a bar and does not appear to be gang 
related, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Homicide detectives are investigating the shooting, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
